Code in Facebook’s smartphone app suggests it is preparing to launch a new chat service called “Talk”, The Information reported. The report stated that the code contains references to parental control features, allowing parents to choose who their child may speak to in the app. Talk will also feature games and “fun masks”. According to the report, the app will be restricted to 13-year-olds and older, and will not require them to have a Facebook account. Facebook declined to comment on the report.